        "His odes are some of them panegyrical, others moral; the rest are jovial or bacchanalian."
    ],
    "etymology": "[F., fr. L. Jovialis pertaining to Jove. The planet Jupiter was thought to make those born under it joyful or jovial. See Jove.]"
